The clock face on the tower is black with gold Roman numerals, and the hands are gold as well. The sky is clear with a few scattered clouds, allowing ample natural light to illuminate the structure. The lighting highlights the texture and details of the stonework, casting subtle shadows that enhance the depth of the image. In the foreground, the calm waters of the River Thames reflect parts of the building, adding a serene element to the scene. The overall composition is balanced, with the tower serving as the central focal point, drawing the viewer's eye upwards. The image captures the grandeur and historical significance of this landmark, set against a tranquil backdrop.

The clock faces are visible, adding a sense of time and history to the scene. In front of the tower, the River Thames is partially visible, with a few small boats or buoys floating on the water, indicating the river's active use. The background of the image features a clear sky with some scattered clouds, providing a serene and open setting that contrasts with the detailed and ornate structure in the foreground.
